gomodel:SYNGO_2649  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" , "Rationale: Fig.2: \"GABAA receptors in synaptic junctions on somata\"\n- \"synapses immunoreactive for the a2 subunit was highest on AISs (Fig.2A and B). Only a fraction of symmetrical synapses on somata, proximal, and distal dendrites showed immunoreactivity for the a2 subunit (Fig. 2C). Immunopositive synapses were also present on the somato-dendritic domain of a subset of GABAergic interneurons in all layers (not shown).\"\n\nAbstract: \". The al subunit has been found in most GABAergic synapses on all postsynaptic domains of pyramidal cells. In contrast, the a2 subunit was located only in a subset of synapses on the somata and dendrites, but in most synapses on axon initial segments innervated by axo-axonic cells.\". Experimental description: \" Five adult Wistar rats were anaesthetized with Sagatal...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2649" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

